 France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William of Goth was born in 1035, in Normandy, France. He had at least 1 daughter with Gunhild Olafsdottir. He died about 1065, in his hometown, at the age of 31."},"et":{"1035–Abt 1065":"1035–umbes 1065","1045–Female":"1045–Surnud","1066–1101":"1066–1101","1740–Female":"1740–Surnud","1035–1065":"1035–1065","Abt 1065":"umbes 1065","1740":"1740","1035":"1035","1101":"1101","1045":"1045","1066":"1066","1065":"1065","Normandie, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1035–Abt 1065":"1035–noin 1065","1045–Female":"1045–Kuollut","1066–1101":"1066–1101","1740–Female":"1740–Kuollut","1035–1065":"1035–1065","Abt 1065":"noin 1065","1740":"1740","1035":"1035","1101":"1101","1045":"1045","1066":"1066","1065":"1065","Normandie, France":"Normandie, Ranska"},"fr":{"1035–Abt 1065":"1035–environ 1065","1045–Female":"1045–Décédée","1066–1101":"1066–1101","1740–Female":"1740–Décédée","1035–1065":"1035–1065","Abt 1065":"environ 1065","1740":"1740","1035":"1035","1101":"1101","1045":"1045","1066":"1066","1065":"1065","Normandie, France":"Normandie, France","lifeSummary":"William of Goth est né en 1035, à Normandie, France. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Gunhild Olafsdottir. Il est décédé e